# ZeroMs (0ms) — Cursor Rules

## Project
Terminal-style typing speed app for CS students and developers.
Stack: Next.js 14 App Router · Tailwind CSS · Zustand · Supabase (@supabase/ssr) · Vercel · TypeScript strict mode

## Design — Non-Negotiable
- Font: JetBrains Mono only (next/font/google)
- Background: #0a0a0a
- Correct chars / primary text: #00ff41
- Error chars: Tailwind red-500
- Untyped chars: Tailwind zinc-600
- NEVER add: cards, box shadows on containers, borders on layout, navbars, footers, modals, toasts
- The UI must feel like a ZSH terminal, not a website

## Component Rules
- Default to server components. Add 'use client' only for hooks, browser APIs, or event handlers.
- No business logic inside components. All calculations live in lib/. Components only read state and render.
- CharacterMap.tsx must always use useMemo — never re-render the full char array without it.
- TypingEngine.tsx is the only file that touches keyboard events.
- Hidden input: position absolute, opacity 0, width 1px, height 1px, pointerEvents none.

## File Ownership
- lib/ — pure functions only. No store imports, no React imports.
- store/ — Zustand only. No component imports.
- components/ — rendering only. Reads from store or props. No calculations.
- app/api/ — route handlers and edge functions only.
- docs/ — markdown documentation only.

## Supabase Rules
- Browser client: createBrowserClient from @supabase/ssr
- Server client: createServerClient + cookies from next/headers
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is server-only. It must never appear in any 'use client' file or be passed to the browser.
- Score inserts only happen inside app/api/verify-score/route.ts using the service role key.
- All other DB reads use the anon key with RLS enforced.

## Anti-Cheat Rules
- The client never writes directly to the leaderboard table.
- All score submission goes through POST /api/verify-score.
- Never expose which anti-cheat check failed in any API response body.
- Shadow ban silently: is_shadowed: true. The user always sees { success: true }.

## Editing Behaviour
- Touch only the files and functions named in the prompt.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.
- Do not add new npm packages without being explicitly asked.
- Do not add explanatory comments unless asked.
- If the prompt is ambiguous, ask one clarifying question before writing code.

## Performance Rules
- CharacterMap useMemo dependency array: [chars, currentIndex, errors] only.
- No async operations inside handleKeystroke — the hot path must be synchronous.
- wpmTimeline and ConsistencyGraph updates happen at most once per second / per keystroke respectively, never more.
- Typing engine latency is the highest priority in the entire codebase. Nothing can make the input feel sluggish.